            <fr:title text="Cantor’s theorem">Cantor’s theorem</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Given any set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, there can be no <fr:link href="/jms-00M8/" title="Surjection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8/" display-uri="jms-00M8" type="local">surjection</fr:link> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>Assume that we <html:em>do</html:em> have a <fr:link href="/jms-00M8/" title="Surjection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8/" display-uri="jms-00M8" type="local">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Consider the subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U\in \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> defined below:</html:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  U = {\mathopen {}\left \{x\in  A\,\middle \vert \,x\not \in  e{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}\right \}\mathclose {}}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/jms-00M8/" title="Surjection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8/" display-uri="jms-00M8" type="local">surjective</fr:link>, we may find some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=U]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>

 <html:p>Thus for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  A]]></fr:tex>, we have
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[
   x\in  e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}
   \Longleftrightarrow 
   x\in  U
   \Longleftrightarrow 
   x\not \in  e{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}
 ]]></fr:tex>. Setting <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:= a]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} \Longleftrightarrow  a\not \in  e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, a contradiction.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
